SUPER USER ROOT : 

    SUPER USER DO : sudo commands

    SWITCH TO ROOT USER : sudo -i

    SWITCH TO USER : sudo su - UserName


NEW USER ACCOUNT :  
    
    ADD SERVICE ACCOUNT USER : sudo useradd UserName

    ADD USER WITH HOME DIRECTORY : sudo useradd -m UserName 

    ADD GENERAL USER : sudo adduser UserName

    CHECK ALL USERS INFO : cat /etc/passwd

    SHOW USER ID AND GROUPS ID : id UserName

    SHOW USER PASSWORDS INFO : cat /etc/shadow

    CHANGE PASSWORD : sudo passwd UserName


EDIT /ETC/SHADOW : sudo chage -Options Arguments UserName


EDIT /ETC/PASSWD : 

    GET DATABASE ENTRY OF USER : getent passwd UserName

    GET INFO ABOUT USER : finger UserName

    CHANGE USER INFO  WITH FINGER : sudo chfn -Options Arguments UserName

    UPDATE INFO IN PASSWD : sudo usermod -Options Arguments UserName


LOCK UNLOCK : 

    LOCK USER ACCOUNT : 
        
        sudo usermod -L UserName
        sudo usermod -s /bin/nologin UserName

    UNLOCK USER ACCOUNT : sudo usermod -U UserName


DELETE USER : 

    DELETE USER NAME : sudo userdel UserName

    DELETE USER :  sudo deluser --remove-home UserName
    

ROOT PREVILAGE : 

    ADD USER TO ROOT : sudo visudo and edit file

    ADD USER TO GROUP SUDO :  sudo usermod -aG sudo UserName


APPENDIX : 

    DIRECTORY : d
    FILE : -
    LINK : l

    READ : r OR 4
    WRITE : w OR 2
    EXECUTE : x OR 1 
    EMPTY : - OR 0

    USER : u
    GROUP : g
    OTHER : o
    ALL : a

    GIVE : +
    TAKE : -

    SETUID : 2
    SETGID : 4
    STICKY BIT : 1


CHANGE PERMISSIONS : 
    
    GIVE ALL PERMISSIONS TO ALL FOR FILE : 

        chmod u=rwx,g=rwx,o=rwx Filename
        chmod ugo=rwx Filename
        chmod 777 Filename

    GIVE ALL PERMISSIONS TO USER AND TAKE FROM GROUP AND OTHER : chmod u+rwx,go-rwx Filename

    TAKE ALL PERMISSIONS FROM ALL : chmod a-rwx Filename

    GIVE PERMISSIONS TO DIRECTORY AND CONTAINED FILES : chmod -R u=rwx,g=rx,o=r 


CHANGE OWNESHIPS : 

    CHANGE GROUP AND OWNER : sudo chown New_Owner:New_Group Filename

    CHANGE OWNER : sudo chown New_Owner Filename

    CHANGE GROUP : sudo chgrp New_Group Filename

    
GROUPS : 

    CHECK A GROUP INFO : getent group GroupName

    CREATE NEW GROUP : sudo groupadd GroupName

    DELETE GROUP : sudo groupdel GroupName

    MODIFY A GROUP : sudo groupmod -Options Arguments GroupName

    CHECK ALL GROUPS : cat /etc/group

    CHECK GROUPS ALL INFO : sudo cat /etc/gshadow

    ADD GROUP ADMIN : sudo gpasswd -A UserName_1,UserName_N GroupName

    ADD GROUP TO USER : sudo usermod -G GroupName UserName

    APPEND USER TO GROUP : sudo usermod -a -G GroupName UserName

    CHANGE MAIN GROUP OF USER : sudo usermod -g GroupName UserName


GROUP ADMIN TASK : 

    ADD NEW USER TO GROUP : gpasswd -a UserName GroupName

    VIEW GROUP INFO : getent group GroupName

    DELETE USER FROM GROUP : gpasswd -d UserName GroupName

    SET GROUP PASSWORD : gpasswd GroupName


ENTER A GROUP WITH GROUP PASSWORD AS TEMPORARY MAIN Group: newgrp GroupName

ALLOW USER TO EXECUTE COMPILED FILE AS OWNER (SETUID) : chmod u+s Filename

ALLOW USER TO CREATE FILE WITH GROUP ID (SETGID) : chmod g+s /Path/To/Folder/Group/


STICKY BIT :

    MAKE DIRECTORY OR FILE WRITE PROTECTED : sudo chmod o+t Path/To/Folder_OR_File


ACCESS CONTROL LIST (+) : 

    GET FILE ACL : getfacl /Path/To/Folder/File

    SET FILE ACL FOR SPECIFIC GROUP : sudo setfacl -m g:GroupName:rwx /Path/To/Folder

    SET FILE ACL FOR SPECIFIC USER : sudo setfacl -m u:UserName:rwx /Path/To/Folder

    SET FILE ACL RECURSIVELY : sudo setfacl -mR g:GroupName:rwx /Path/To/Folder

    SET FILE ACL DEFAULT FOR NEWLY ADDED FOLDER OR FILE OR USER : sudo setfacl -md g:GroupName:rwx /Path/To/Folder

    REMOVE DEFAULT ACL PERMISSIONS : sudo setfacl -k /Path/To/Folder

    REMOVE FILE ACL FOR SPECIFIC USER : suso facl -x u:UserName ath/To/Folder

    REMOVE FILE ACL FOR ALL FILES : suso facl -Rb Path/To/Folder/


FILE ATTRIBUTES : 

    LIST FILE ATTRIBUTES : lsattr Path/To/File

    MAKE FILE IMMUTABLE : sudo chattr +i Path/To/Fil

    MAKE FILE APPEND ONLY : sudo chattr +a Path/To/File

    MAKE WHOLE DIRECTORY IMMUTABLE : sudo chattr -R +i Path/To/Folder/

    MAKE WHOLE DIRECTORY APPEND ONLY : sudo chattr -R +a Path/To/Folder/















    